### 2. Lombok Incompatible with Java 25
The system runs **Java 25.0.2**. All released Lombok versions use `sun.misc.Unsafe::objectFieldOffset`
which is terminally deprecated in Java 25, causing:
```
Fatal error compiling: java.lang.ExceptionInInitializerError: com.sun.tools.javac.code.TypeTag :: UNKNOWN
```
**Fix:** Removed Lombok from [pom.xml](file:///c:/Users/BHAVESH/Downloads/realtime-sync-engine/realtime-sync-engine/pom.xml) entirely. Rewrote all files with explicit constructors,
getters/setters, manual builder patterns, and `LoggerFactory.getLogger()`.

### 3. JavaScript Bug in Frontend ([index.html](file:///c:/Users/BHAVESH/Downloads/realtime-sync-engine/src/main/resources/static/index.html))
In [loadDocument()](file:///c:/Users/BHAVESH/Downloads/realtime-sync-engine/realtime-sync-engine/src/main/resources/static/js/index.html#370-408), the STOMP subscribe callback used [document](file:///c:/Users/BHAVESH/Downloads/realtime-sync-engine/realtime-sync-engine/src/main/java/com/sync/engine/entity/SyncOperation.java#82-86) as the parameter name, which
shadowed the global `window.document`, breaking all `getElementById()` calls inside it.
**Fix:** Renamed parameter to `msg`.

### 4. Frontend in Wrong Location
The HTML was at [static/js/index.html](file:///c:/Users/BHAVESH/Downloads/realtime-sync-engine/realtime-sync-engine/src/main/resources/static/js/index.html) instead of [static/index.html](file:///c:/Users/BHAVESH/Downloads/realtime-sync-engine/src/main/resources/static/index.html).
**Fix:** Created at the correct location.

### 5. RabbitMQ + Debezium Startup Fixes
Added to [application.properties](file:///c:/Users/BHAVESH/Downloads/realtime-sync-engine/realtime-sync-engine/src/main/resources/application.properties):
```properties
spring.autoconfigure.exclude=org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.amqp.RabbitAutoConfiguration
debezium.enabled=false
```

### 6. Debezium Type Fix
Switched `DebeziumEngine.create(Connect.class)` → `Json.class` to match `ChangeEvent<String, String>`.

